  "text": "We consider a set of n periodic or sporadic tasks that have to be scheduled on a single processor with voltage control capabilities. A task τ i is a sequence of jobs τ i,k (k = 1, 2, . . .), each characterized by a number C i of worstcase execution cycles (WCECs), a minimum interarrival time T i (often referred to as the task period), and a relative deadline D i ≤ T i . Tasks are fully preemptive and do not perform blocking operations. Note that intertask communication can still be performed using non-blocking mechanisms, as Cyclic Asynchronous Buffers [CITATION_1] .",
